The paper deals with signal processing on graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on iterative methods for reconstructing bandlimited graph signals from sampled data suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Signal Processing (cs.SP).
